25|$|On 29 January, the LJM and JEM leaders {{issued a}} joint {{statement}} affirming {{their commitment to the}} Doha negotiations and intention to attend the Doha forum on 5 February. The <b>Sudanese</b> <b>government</b> postponed decision to attend the forum due to beliefs that an internal peace process without the involvement of rebel groups might be possible. Later in February, the <b>Sudanese</b> <b>Government</b> agreed to return to Doha with a view to complete a new peace agreement {{by the end of that}} month. On 25 February, both LJM and JEM announced that they had rejected the peace document proposed by the mediators in Doha. The main sticking points were the issues of a Darfuri vice-president and compensation for victims. The <b>Sudanese</b> <b>government</b> did not comment on the peace document.|$|E
