50|$|Mahjoub Sharif (1 January 1948 - 2 April 2014), born as Mahjoub Muhammad Sharif Muhammad, was a Sudanese poet, {{teacher and}} activist.He became known in Sudan and other Arabic-speaking {{countries}} for his colloquial poetry and his public engagement, both committed {{to further the}} causes of democracy, freedom, general well-being and national identity. His poetry was put to music by eminent musicians, such as Mohammed Wardi and Mohamed Mounir, but also led to repeated political imprisonment under different <b>Sudanese</b> <b>governments.</b>|$|R
